TableI reports how our proposal could promote state-of-the-art (SOTA) approaches in guiding students
, including KD-Net[12], PMKL[1], ProtoKD[13] and SMU-Net[11]. When three modalities (the most challenging setting) are missing, the anchor PmixsubscriptsuperscriptP^{*}_{mix}italic_P start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT  end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_m italic_i italic_x end_POSTSUBSCRIPT, could lead to an improvement of 1.75 dice score on average for various SOTA students. We also carry out experiments on other less difficult scenarios. These additional results can be referred to in TableIII.

Options of anchors.
TableI also shows that students trained by teachers with PmixsubscriptsuperscriptP^{*}_{mix}italic_P start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT  end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_m italic_i italic_x end_POSTSUBSCRIPT performs better than teachers with PmixksubscriptsuperscriptP^{k}_{mix}italic_P start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT italic_k end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_m italic_i italic_x end_POSTSUBSCRIPT; in addition, teachers with PmixNsubscriptsuperscriptP^{N}_{mix}italic_P start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT italic_N end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_m italic_i italic_x end_POSTSUBSCRIPT is the worst one.
PmixsubscriptsuperscriptP^{*}_{mix}italic_P start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT  end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_m italic_i italic_x end_POSTSUBSCRIPT brings an improvement on students by 1.75 dice score on average while PmixksubscriptsuperscriptP^{k}_{mix}italic_P start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT italic_k end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_m italic_i italic_x end_POSTSUBSCRIPT brings 1.28.
Visualized demonstrations of aligning the latent representations to different anchors are displayed in Figure2.
In Figure3, visualization results of the latent space for a specific sample are also shown.
As observed, teachers with PmixNsubscriptsuperscriptP^{N}_{mix}italic_P start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT italic_N end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_m italic_i italic_x end_POSTSUBSCRIPT and PmixsubscriptsuperscriptP^{*}_{mix}italic_P start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT  end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_m italic_i italic_x end_POSTSUBSCRIPT are more sensitive to small targets (yellow boxes).
